I want to start by saying thank you for allowing me this opportunity to express myself. From my perspective, collaboration and healthy rivalry are the two main keys to success.
When a task is completed collaboratively, it signifies that everyone involved in the project must work together to avoid disaster. For instance, if we compete with one another during a group project in an effort to finish it first, we may unintentionally make a mistake that makes the team project fail rather than our individual job. The most important aspect of those activities is teamwork, with healthy competition focused on "quality of works," which refers to who does the best work.

But at the same time work without any competition would not lead to greater output. It leads to some kind of laziness and thought that they will definitely finish the work . It is one of the most wrongest thing.It is important to have some kind of healthy competiotion without any bad intention. 

       So I would like to say, it is more imortant to have cooperation more than competion to acheive more success. Onca again thank you for giving me the oppurtunity to express my thoughts.
